1##Show kernel version and system architecture      ##uname -a

2##Show name and version of distribution            ##head -n1 /etc/issue

3##Show all partitions registered on the system     ##cat /proc/partitions

4##Show RAM total seen by the system                ##grep MemTotal /proc/meminfo

5##Show CPU(s) info                                 ##grep "model name" /proc/cpuinfo

6##Show PCI info                                    ##lspci -tv

7##Show USB info                                    ##lsusb -tv

8##List mounted filesystems on the system           ##mount | column -t

9##Show system reboot history                       ##last reboot

a##Show amount of (remaining) RAM                   ##free -m

b##Show free space on mounted filesystems           ##df -h

## Notes------------------------------------------------------------------------
* fdisk -l	Show disks partitions sizes and types (run as root)
